{
  "text": "Definition 2.1 [CITATION_1] Let E be the set of parameters, U be an initial universe. Consider P(U) as a set of all subsets of U and A as a subset of E. A pair (F,A) is called a soft set over U where F : A \u2192 P(U) is a setvalued function.In an other words, the soft set is a parametrized family of subsets of the set U. For every e \u2208 U, F(e) may be considered as a eapproximate elements of the soft set (F, A). [CITATION_2] A soft set (F,A) over U is said to be a Null soft set denoted by \u03a6, if for every \u03b5 \u2208 A, F(\u03b5)=\u2205. Definition 2.3 [CITATION_3] For two soft sets (F,A) and (G,B) over a common universe U we say that (F,A) is a soft subset of (G,B) if i)",
